# Use FVM, Not Raw Flutter/Dart CLI

This project uses [FVM](https://fvm.app/) to pin the Flutter SDK. **Always** invoke Flutter and Dart through FVM so the correct SDK version runs.

## Commands

Prefix every Flutter or Dart CLI invocation with `fvm`:

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `flutter ...` | `fvm flutter ...` |
| `dart ...` | `fvm dart ...` |

Examples:

```bash
# BAD
flutter pub get
flutter analyze
flutter test
dart run build_runner build

# GOOD
fvm flutter pub get
fvm flutter analyze
fvm flutter test
fvm dart run build_runner build
```

## Agent behavior

- When suggesting or running shell commands for this repo, use `fvm flutter` / `fvm dart`.
- Do not assume a global `flutter` on PATH is the project SDK.

If FVM is not installed, document that the user should install FVM and run `fvm use` per project docs rather than switching to raw `flutter` as the default workflow.
